## 2. Architecture Registry Deployment

### 2.1 Registry Installation

**Step 1: Prepare Registry Storage**

```bash
# Create Kubernetes secret for registry encryption
kubectl create secret generic architecture-registry-key \
  --from-literal=encryption-key=$(openssl rand -base64 32) \
  -n indestructible-autoops

# Create persistent volume for registry storage
kubectl apply -f - <<EOF
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: architecture-registry-pvc
  namespace: indestructible-autoops
spec:
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteMany
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: 50Gi
  storageClassName: fast-ssd
EOF
```

**Step 2: Deploy Registry Service**

```bash
# Deploy Architecture Registry service
kubectl apply -f architecture_registry_deployment.yaml

# Wait for pods to be ready
kubectl wait --for=condition=ready pod \
  -l app=architecture-registry \
  -n indestructible-autoops \
  --timeout=300s

# Verify service is accessible
curl -s http://architecture-registry:8000/health
```

**Step 3: Load Registry Data**

```bash
# Load architecture_registry.yaml into database
curl -X POST http://architecture-registry:8000/api/v1/registry/load \
  -H "Content-Type: application/yaml" \
  -d @architecture_registry.yaml

# Verify registry is loaded
curl -s http://architecture-registry:8000/api/v1/registry/status
```

### 2.2 Validation Procedures

```bash
# Run validation tests
kubectl exec -it \
  $(kubectl get pod -l app=architecture-registry -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}') \
  -n indestructible-autoops \
  -- python -m pytest tests/validation/test_architecture_registry.py -v

# Check consistency
curl -s http://architecture-registry:8000/api/v1/validate/consistency \
  | jq '.validationStatus'

# Generate mapping report
curl -s http://architecture-registry:8000/api/v1/registry/mapping-report \
  > architecture_mapping_report.json
```

**Expected Output:** All validation tests pass, consistency score > 95%

### 2.3 Success Criteria

- [ ] Registry service responding to health checks
- [ ] All layers (L1-L5) properly registered
- [ ] All domains (D1-D4) properly registered
- [ ] All capabilities (C1-C13) properly registered
- [ ] All components (COMP-BE-1 to COMP-BE-10, COMP-FE-1 to COMP-FE-8) registered
- [ ] Dependency graph has no circular dependencies
- [ ] Component test coverage > 95%
- [ ] Registry accessible via API

