## 3. Governance Registry Deployment

### 3.1 Registry Installation

**Step 1: Prepare Governance Storage and Cryptographic Keys**

```bash
# Generate RSA-4096 key pair for digital signatures
openssl genrsa -out private_key.pem 4096
openssl rsa -in private_key.pem -pubout -out public_key.pem

# Create Kubernetes secrets for cryptographic keys
kubectl create secret generic governance-registry-keys \
  --from-file=private_key=private_key.pem \
  --from-file=public_key=public_key.pem \
  -n indestructible-autoops

# Create secret for hash algorithm seeds
kubectl create secret generic governance-hash-seeds \
  --from-literal=sha256-seed=$(openssl rand -hex 32) \
  --from-literal=sha512-seed=$(openssl rand -hex 32) \
  -n indestructible-autoops
```

**Step 2: Deploy Governance Registry Service**

```bash
# Deploy Governance Registry
kubectl apply -f governance_registry_deployment.yaml

# Wait for pods to be ready
kubectl wait --for=condition=ready pod \
  -l app=governance-registry \
  -n indestructible-autoops \
  --timeout=300s

# Verify service
curl -s http://governance-registry:8001/health
```

**Step 3: Load Governance Policies**

```bash
# Load governance_registry.yaml
curl -X POST http://governance-registry:8001/api/v1/policies/load \
  -H "Content-Type: application/yaml" \
  -d @governance_registry.yaml

# Verify GLCM modules are loaded
curl -s http://governance-registry:8001/api/v1/glcm/modules \
  | jq '.modules | length'
# Expected: 5 (GLCM-NAR, GLCM-FCT, GLCM-UNC, GLCM-EVC, GLCM-Auto)
```

### 3.2 GLCM Module Verification

```bash
# Test GLCM-NAR (Narrative-Free Enforcement)
curl -X POST http://governance-registry:8001/api/v1/glcm/nar/test \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"text": "The system was very critically impacted"}'
# Expected: VIOLATION - contains "very" and "critically"

# Test GLCM-EVC (Evidence Chain)
curl -X POST http://governance-registry:8001/api/v1/glcm/evc/verify-chain \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d @test_evidence_chain.json
# Expected: VALID if chain is unbroken

# Test GLCM-FCT (False Timeline Detection)
curl -X POST http://governance-registry:8001/api/v1/glcm/fct/verify-timeline \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d @test_timeline.json
# Expected: VALID if timeline is monotonic
```

### 3.3 Compliance Framework Mapping Verification

```bash
# Verify NIST 800-53 mapping
curl -s http://governance-registry:8001/api/v1/compliance/nist-800-53/coverage \
  | jq '.coverage_percentage'
# Expected: > 95%

# Verify ISO 27001 mapping
curl -s http://governance-registry:8001/api/v1/compliance/iso-27001/coverage \
  | jq '.coverage_percentage'
# Expected: > 95%

# Generate compliance report
curl -s http://governance-registry:8001/api/v1/compliance/report \
  > governance_compliance_report.json
```

### 3.4 Success Criteria

- [ ] All 5 GLCM modules operational
- [ ] Hash chain verification working (SHA-256, SHA-512, BLAKE2b)
- [ ] Canonicalization rules applied correctly
- [ ] Evidence specification enforced
- [ ] Replay capability functional
- [ ] Compliance mappings verified for all frameworks
- [ ] Digital signatures validated
- [ ] Governance policies applied consistently

