## 4. Execution Registry Deployment

### 4.1 Registry Installation

**Step 1: Deploy Execution Registry Service**

```bash
# Deploy Execution Registry
kubectl apply -f execution_registry_deployment.yaml

# Wait for pods
kubectl wait --for=condition=ready pod \
  -l app=execution-registry \
  -n indestructible-autoops \
  --timeout=300s

# Verify service
curl -s http://execution-registry:8002/health
```

**Step 2: Load Execution Policies and Schedules**

```bash
# Load execution_registry.yaml
curl -X POST http://execution-registry:8002/api/v1/registry/load \
  -H "Content-Type: application/yaml" \
  -d @execution_registry.yaml

# Verify phases are loaded
curl -s http://execution-registry:8002/api/v1/phases \
  | jq '.phases | length'
# Expected: 3 (Era-1, Era-2, Era-3)

# Verify stages are loaded
curl -s http://execution-registry:8002/api/v1/stages \
  | jq '.stages | length'
# Expected: 5 (S1-S5)
```

**Step 3: Configure Environments**

```bash
# Configure environment enforcement policies
kubectl apply -f execution_environment_configs.yaml

# Verify environments
curl -s http://execution-registry:8002/api/v1/environments \
  | jq '.environments | length'
# Expected: 5 (Local, CI, Staging, Production, Audit)

# Set enforcement level per environment
curl -X PUT http://execution-registry:8002/api/v1/environments/production/enforcement \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"level": "CRITICAL"}'
```

### 4.2 Phase Progression Configuration

```bash
# Set Era-1 start conditions
curl -X POST http://execution-registry:8002/api/v1/phases/Era-1/activate \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "startTime": "2026-02-05T12:00:00Z",
    "autoPromote": false,
    "requireApproval": false
  }'

# Configure Era-2 prerequisites
curl -X PUT http://execution-registry:8002/api/v1/phases/Era-2/prerequisites \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "requiredCompletions": ["Era-1"],
    "requiredSuccessCriteria": {
      "evidence_collection": "> 99%",
      "hash_chain_integrity": "> 99.9%",
      "detection_rate": "> 95%"
    }
  }'
```

### 4.3 Track Scheduling

```bash
# Schedule parallel tracks
curl -X POST http://execution-registry:8002/api/v1/tracks/schedule \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "tracks": [
      {"id": "TrackA", "startWeek": 1, "duration": 4},
      {"id": "TrackB", "startWeek": 1, "duration": 4},
      {"id": "TrackC", "startWeek": 1, "duration": 3},
      {"id": "TrackD", "startWeek": 5, "duration": 3},
      {"id": "TrackE", "startWeek": 7, "duration": 4}
    ]
  }'

# Verify track dependencies
curl -s http://execution-registry:8002/api/v1/tracks/dependencies \
  | jq '.valid'
# Expected: true (no circular dependencies)
```

### 4.4 Success Criteria

- [ ] All phases (Era-1, Era-2, Era-3) configured
- [ ] All stages (S1-S5) configured
- [ ] All tracks (A-E) scheduled
- [ ] All environments (Local, CI, Staging, Production, Audit) configured
- [ ] Phase progression requirements defined
- [ ] Rollback procedures documented
- [ ] Deployment policies enforced
- [ ] Stage transition criteria verified

