## 5. Cross-Registry Validation

### 5.1 Automated Consistency Checks

```bash
# Run comprehensive cross-registry validation
curl -X POST http://governance-registry:8001/api/v1/validate/cross-registry \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d @cross_registry_mapping.yaml

# Expected output: all checks pass
# {
#   "validationStatus": "PASSED",
#   "checksCompleted": 47,
#   "checksGreen": 47,
#   "checksYellow": 0,
#   "checksRed": 0
# }
```

### 5.2 Mapping Verification

```bash
# Verify capability-to-component mapping
curl -s http://architecture-registry:8000/api/v1/mappings/capability-to-component \
  | jq '.unmapped_capabilities'
# Expected: [] (empty array, all capabilities have components)

# Verify capability-to-governance mapping
curl -s http://governance-registry:8001/api/v1/mappings/capability-to-governance \
  | jq '.unmapped_capabilities'
# Expected: [] (empty array)

# Verify governance-to-compliance mapping
curl -s http://governance-registry:8001/api/v1/compliance/coverage-analysis \
  | jq '.uncovered_controls'
# Expected: [] (empty array)
```

### 5.3 Dependency Graph Validation

```bash
# Verify no circular dependencies
curl -X POST http://execution-registry:8002/api/v1/validate/no-cycles \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d @cross_registry_mapping.yaml

# Generate dependency report
curl -s http://execution-registry:8002/api/v1/dependencies/graph \
  > dependency_graph.json

# Visualize with Graphviz
jq -r '.edges[]' dependency_graph.json | \
  awk '{print "\"" $1 "\" -> \"" $2 "\""}' > graph.dot
dot -Tpng graph.dot -o graph.png
```

### 5.4 Success Criteria

- [ ] All consistency checks pass (0 red, 0 yellow)
- [ ] All capability-to-component mappings verified
- [ ] All capability-to-governance mappings verified
- [ ] All compliance framework mappings verified
- [ ] No circular dependencies detected
- [ ] Cross-registry mapping report complete
- [ ] Ready for Era-1 deployment

